Part I - (Dataset Exploration Title)¶

by (Oluwatosin K.)¶

Introduction¶

This data set contains 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, interest rate, current loan status, borrower income, and many others. We would be exploring this dataset to find useful insights on borrowers and to observe if there are any notable patterns.

9 Loan Status Distribution VS Listing Category¶

In [24]:
def loanstatuts (filter_var,title) :
    df_loan.query(filter_var).LoanStatus.value_counts(sort=True).plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title(title, fontsize=20)
    plt.xticks(fontsize=12)
    plt.yticks(fontsize=12);

Conclusions¶

Many Calofornians live off loans trying to pay other debts, inspite of being one of the states with higher income ranges.

I observed a higher current Loan status for people within the debt consolidation category.

Only a few people pay within a year, majority of the Borrowers find it comfortable to payback within a 3 year/ 36-month payback period.

I observed that the median Original Loan amount Increases with Increase in income range of members.

Fewer higher earners of 75,000 dollars and above took loans compared to those below the median earning range.
